You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Analytics > Filter a Dashboard

Filtering rules apply to fields from the dashboard’s source reports. Filters can be used on text, numeric, date, and datetime fields and on picklists, lookups, and checkboxes.

Filters have a name, operator, and up to 50 values. They must be included in the source report’s layout.

When filtering, keep these considerations in mind:
Fields that are used in a dashboard filter must be included in the source report’s layout.
You can’t add filters to dashboards with Visualforce or s-control widgets.
Filters aren’t applied when scheduling or emailing a dashboard.
Filtering isn’t supported for widgets created from joined report charts.

To create a filter, select a field and specify values. The filtered view is preserved so that the next time you see the dashboard, data is filtered in the same way.

You can also apply filters using URL parameters in Lightning Experience to customize your dashboard views. For example, you can create URLs for different account owners or to zero in on closed deals.

Dashboard filters make it easy for users to visualize data from different perspectives by applying filters based on source report fields.
